description: The continuing adventures of Nate Torres, a teenager who always thought of himself as a quitter--until he entered the world of street basketball. Sapporo has become overrun with thousands of student athletes all thirsting for the chance to come out victorious in Japan's National Basketball Championships. Representing Tokyo in the competition, The Jonan High School varsity basketball team has beat the odds in getting there and won't leave without the pennant. But they'll soon learn that playing against the kids in their neighborhood pales in comparison to the kind of game the thugs and pros at the championships will give them. Right off the plane, they find themselves staring down the nostrils of the Kyan Marine Industry team, a burly collection of tanned rough necks who plan on knocking off any team that stands in their way. But Jonan has heart, they have determination and, with a little luck, this team might just do Tokyo proud...as long as they don't get distracted by the tourists spots, the shopping and the girls schools!
name: Vol. 1

description: In the thick of the game, Kobayashi sinks another two pointer and puts the Jonan team back in the running against the favorites from Okinawa. But the Okinawa team is tough, and they play a rough game--but enough is enough. Even if they're 25 points up at the half, Okinawa hasn't seen the last of Jonan. Jonan loses a little hope with the realization that they've never come up from behind before. Underdogs, however, need to believe that they're never out of a game, no matter how far they fall behind...
name: Vol. 2

description: Johnan High got through the first round, but now they're up against their archrivals, Tsukuba High. But before plunging into the second round, there are some unresolved emotional conflicts that have to be addressed. The chief reason for the rivalry with Tsukuba dates back to last season when Tsukuba drove Imagawa of Johnan out of the game for good with an injury. He now serves somewhat bitterly as the team's manager. Personal demons also threaten the cohesion of Johnan. When Nate recognizes Sawamura's long lost father working as a doorman in Sapporo, the cool-as-ice pretty boy may not be able to handle the pressure.
name: Vol. 3

description: It's finally here: the big game against Nango Daitsukuba High School in Ibaraki...the team that knocked Johnan out of the tournament in the first round last year. Johnan has already beaten Kyan Marine Industry High School in the first round and are coming into the second round with a little more confidence. They know that if they lose tonight, they're on the first plane back to Tokyo, but what could possibly shake this stalwart team? Well, Sawamura's long-lost father sets Johnan's starting guard a little on edge. And has Nate discovered girls?
name: Vol. 4

description: Johnan has never been more ready to take on Tskuba, the very team that knocked them out of the finals in the first round last year. They've trained, they've hustled, they've shown tremendous teamwork. What could possibly go wrong? Well, Sawamura ran off to go confront the father that abandoned him years ago and isn't back for the game; Sherman's ankle is giving him the kind of trouble that ends basketball careers; and the surge of excitement the team felt going into the finals has soured. Thank goodness for Nate who seems to be playing the game of his life. Even Takagi, the ace of Tskuba notices the young Nate's abilities, and is thoroughly impressed. But not everyone on Tskuba is a true sportsman. Mikami may try to exploit Sherman's injury by creating a little 'accident' for the Johnan center. But will the rest of Mikami's team go along with his win-at-all-cost philosophy?
name: Vol. 5

description: Johnan's into the third round of the National Championships, and the team gets some much needed R&R. Nate hooks up again with Tomomi and the two continue their courtship at the zoo where they agree to meet to see the monkeys. But the rest of the boys decide to do what they do best...hit the streets and cruise for skirt. However, they all get a little more than they bargained for when Kusuda, a tough girl with a mean drive on the streetball courts, entices the Johnan tribe into a bit of a scrimmage. And, man, will she give them all a shock.
name: Vol. 6

description: With a few games behind them, the question now comes down to whether Johnan can keep up its incredible momentum. The team is eager to match up against Kanakita Northern Industry High School - the tournament favorites - but first they've got to face--and beat--Yokohama Kokusai Shougyou. Even if they do, however, they're at a loss for a strategy against the seemingly unbeatable Kanakita. Off the court, things are getting particularly interesting for Nate and Tomomi who go on a date to the zoo to see the monkeys. Ah, young love...
name: Vol. 7

description: As game day approaches, everyone is working on their full-court strategy. While Kuwata and Kobayashi devise a game plan, Nate tries to perfect his stroke from beyond the arc. Across court, Amami and the massive Yuza argue about the best way to take down Johnan. When the tournament arrives, everyone puts on his game face. As the pressure in the paint threatens to erupt into a basket-brawl, it's no time to lose heart!
name: Vol. 8

description: Game day is here, and things look good as Johnan wins the opening tip-off. Nate gets a good look at the hoop and goes in for his famous Air Walk--only to be slammed by the super-rookie Amami! Johnan suddenly find themselves without answers to the swarming defense. With time running out in the tournament, Umakure decides to step up and show why he is the captain of this squad.
name: Vol. 9

description: It's halftime in the big game and the score is 43 to 34 with Kana Kita in the lead! But things go from bad to worse as Yuza dazzles the crowd with his dynamic dribbling, dunking and defense. Can Nate and Sawamura get in their groove and make some spectacular plays of their own in spite of Sawamura's injured arm? Or will it be time for Johnan to throw in the towel?
name: Vol. 10

description:
With the tournament over for Johnan, the team says goodbye to its fans, and then spends a day at the beach Johnan-style! Crazy antics ensue as the guys find out Kasahari works there for a summer job, Miz loses her top, Shurman is seen on a date and the crew faces ghosts from the hot springs!

Chapter Titles

  • Episode 86 - See Ya!
  • Episode 87 - Loose Ends
  • Episode 88 - Sweet Memories
  • Episode 89 - Letters From Nate
  • Episode 90 - Beach Blanket Bonanza
  • Episode 91 - Summer Lovin'
  • Episode 92 - Stand My Me
  • Episode 93 - Bump In the Night
  • Sawamura Special - Multiplicity
name: Vol. 11

description:
When the team boards a plane heading for the tournament, they try to loosen up by taking their antics with them. With dozens of teams in the competition, one loss will send the loser packing. Tensions run high--who will come out victorious and be declared the best of the best?

Chapter Titles

  • Episode 94 - Passing the Baton
  • Episode 95 - Rebels Without A Ball
  • Episode 96 - Choices
  • Episode 97 - To Every Season
  • Episode 98 - Typhoon Mary
  • Episode 99 - Behind The Smile
  • Episode 100 - Deep Down
  • Spin-off Episode: True Confessions of Kim Yabe
name: Vol. 12

description: When a mysterious girl named Risa shows up at Three Slam, Scratch ends up having to play a basketball "rope match" to keep her brother from dragging her back to Akihabara. What's a basketball "rope match"? Well, it's when members of the opposing teams are bound to each other with a rope as they play the game. Fun stuff. But when it's all over, Sawamura returns home to a startling and eventually violent reunion with none other than his old acquaintance, Joker.
name: Vol. 13

description: Scratch is doing well enough in the 3-on-3 tournament, but the joke might just be on Johnan. When they're set to face off against Joker on the court, it turns out there's a whole other side to Sawamura they haven't seen yet. Injured, Nate must beat the entire group in order for Scratch to move on in this twisted tournament.
name: Vol. 14

description:
The next round features a 3 on 2 match between Scratch and Caney G. If Scratch wins, Sawamura will return to Scratch. But it isn't going to be easy for Nate and the team, since Sawamura and his partner already know all of Scratch's weaknesses. And even if they can win, one more team--Sanctuary--stands in their way, on and off the court.

Chapter Titles

  • Episode 118 - A Real Reality
  • Episode 119 - It's Not Basketball If It's Not Fun!
  • Episode 120 - A Pure Promise
  • Episode 121 - The Return of Shu
  • Episode 122 - Nate's Feelings, Sawamura's Heart
  • Episode 123 - A Vow Under A Starry Sky
  • Episode 124 - The Look of Fear
  • Episode 125 - We Need A Hero
  • Episode 126 - An Unexpected End
name: Vol. 15

description:
The Winter Cup is about to start in Tokyo and Tomomi has to be ready for the competition. She is so excited to see Nate again that focusing on the game is becoming increasingly difficult. Will Nates moves on and off the court be enough to move Tomomi in his direction? Seems like Nate may be facing some double dribble action for the big game!

Chapter Titles

  • Episode 127 - We'll Meet Again In Tokyo
  • Episode 128 - Troublesome Boy
  • Episode 129 - Love Sensation
  • Episode 130 - Clash! Unohara vs. Tsukuba
  • Episode 131 - Battle On the Court
  • Episode 132 - Winner
  • Episode 133 - Kobayashi's Ordeals
  • Episode 134 - Show It! Johnan's Spirit
  • Episode 135 - The Rival
name: Vol. 16

description:
Felicia is set to play Seijo at the Winter Cup Tournament, but soon after the game starts, Hiroko starts acting strangely.. Coach Miyauchi has a surprise for the team and it doesn't look good. Nate and Masaki team up to save the game for Felicia! Nate finally kicks his insecurities to the curb. Will Tomomi finally see him for who he really is?

Chapter Titles

  • Episode 136 - Battle of the Goddesses
  • Episode 137 - Don't Stop Fighting!
  • Episode 138 - The Last Minute Drama
  • Episode 139 - Cinderella Victory
  • Episode 140 - Because It's Christmas Eve
  • Episode 141 - Merry Christmas!
  • Episode 142 - Big Clean Noisy Song
  • Episode 143 - Especially Friends
  • Episode 144 - Love Game
name: Vol. 17

description: Kobayashi and Sawamura are getting along even worse than ever, and Nate comes up with a scheme to make Sawamura see that Kobayashi cares about him, even though he doesn't show it. When Jonan can't win because of low average scores of the subs, Nate rounds everyone up every morning for extra practice time, which ends up paying off--but at what price?
name: Vol. 18

description: JD lives a peaceful life with his grandfather on a small island, until bounty hunters show up looking for them! Will JD be able to put to use what his grandfather’s taught him to survive in a world of magical peril? And what is the nature of the Recast spell his grandfather’s cast on him?
name: Vol. 1

description: The mighty bounty hunter Du Mascara has cornered JD, which is good and bad news. The good news is that Du Mascara is the least of JD's trouble. The bad news is he must jump off a cliff in order to escape this killer. Jumping doesn't look so bad--until you have to face a seal monster. The seal monster has a special message for JD. He must either heed this message or trust his own instincts.
name: Vol. 2

description: JD finally meets Blaise, the lord his grandfather told him to seek. But Blaise surprises JD by telling him that he can't be of any help--and he leaves JD in the hands of an angry mob of townspeople. An incident involving JD's grandfather seems to be the source of Blaise's grumpiness, and maybe the cause of a premature end to JD's adventures!
name: Vol. 3

description: JD and Blaise seal away Blaise's sister Carmen and go off to search for Lupus the Wolf, the only one who can undo the curse on her. But Lupus the Wolf has been dead for twelve years! When they find out that there might be another werewolf nearby, will they find him before monster hunters do?
name: Vol. 4

description: Everything seems to have gone wrong--JD and Blaise can't reach Carmen before Zaha kills her. Eomaia allows Zaha to die, then declares a war of retaliation against the whole Jade Region! When the cruel goddess unleashes her monsters of war against the peaceful world, it's up to JD and Blaise to stop her reign of terror!
name: Vol. 5

description: The grand finale--it's the end of JD's adventure, but just the beginning of his tale. All this time, JD's been trying to get to the Fourth World. That was his grandfather Grifford's last request, and JD and others around him have begun to notice that his powers resemble those of Fourth World royalty. But the only way to get there is by passing through Volcano Laten in the hide of the monster Gorgon. And the only way to Gorgon is through the sorceress who controls him. When he finds her, though, he discovers much more than just Gorgon's whereabouts...Follow JD as he embarks on a final journey to claim his destiny!
name: Vol. 6

description:
Kokaku ventures on a quest to find the hottest chili pepper, taking him to Edo, but what he discovers instead is that he holds no reputation within the city. If he wants to get things done and carry out justice like a true hero, he’ll have to do it the old fashioned way--with a good whopping! Things don’t go as planned when Shikki (Turtle) appears and their ideologies continue to clash, not to mention their swords! Being the hero isn’t always easy, and as Kokaku will learn, sometimes those that need help are the ones closest to you.

Chapter Titles

  • 10th Subject: The Volume of Grus, The Crane
  • 11th Subject: The Volume of the Oriental Crane
  • 12th Subject: The Volume of Tsurumi
  • Side Story 1: The Volume of the Crane's Cry
  • Side Story 2: The Volume of the Crane's Beak
  • Extra: The Volume of Shikki's Secret Diary
name: Vol. 3

description:
When a group of seven young college students go off to enjoy a weekend getaway at a remote mountain villa, secrets that haunt the friends are unveiled--which lead to bizarre love triangles, tragic relationships, and deadly betrayal. And when hallucinations and strange disappearances begin, their dream vacation turns into a nightmare...

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 1: The Mountain Villa
  • Chapter 2: Crew
  • Chapter 3: Laughingstock
  • Chapter 4: Punk
  • Chapter 5: Party
  • Chapter 6: Fooled!
name: Vol. 1

description:
Friendships begin to go sour between the crew--all starting with the fiasco that happens in this volume! Taein sits around in the kitchen dreading what is just beginning to unfold: Gihu comes in and has a small chat with Taein, telling Taein that he's trying too hard to be nice to everyone, and that's it's impossible to be the everlasting nice guy to everyone and every time. We see a clash between Jueun and Ha, and a mysterious connection between the two is revealed!

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 1: Silent Midnight
  • Chapter 2: Heartbreak
  • Chapter 3: Her Ghost in the Forest
  • Chapter 4: Vanitas
  • Chapter 5: Deja Vu
  • Chapter 6: Past Come True
name: Vol. 2

description:
The secrets of the crew are finally coming to light, even as the body count rises. We learn the history of Ha and Jueun. Taein realizes Hyeri had sent a dying message to the crew. And Gihu explains a horrifying incident that happened years ago...and now has come back to haunt them all.

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 1: Bloody Bride
  • Chapter 2: Eyes of R.E.D.R.U.M.
  • Chapter 3: Flash Back I
  • Chapter 4: Flash Back II
  • Chapter 5: Requiem
  • Chapter 6: Silent Anthology
name: Vol. 3
The life of a king and conqueror

description: The world's deadliest mutant, he's been called the best there is; now, the best of the best Wolverine stories ever told are collected in one deluxe hardcover! In Claremont and Miller's WOLVERINE, Logan goes solo when he travels to Japan, testing his honor and risking his life for the only woman he's ever loved. In Windsor-Smith's WEAPON X, Wolverine is subjected to a series of sadistic medical experiments designed to create the perfect soldier long before his days as an X-Man. Also collecting INCREDIBLE HULK #181, UNCANNY X-MEN #205 and CAPTAIN AMERICA ANNUAL #8!
name: Volume One

first_appearance_locations.name: New Charles Xavier School for Mutants

location_credits.name: New Charles Xavier School for Mutants

description: Learn the secret of how the Astonishing X-Men’s diamond-sculpted seductress, Emma Frost, became the formidable woman she is today. Witness the first time her mutant powers manifested, her difficulties at home and in school, and her early first love that explains how she blossomed from an innocent teenager into the wealthy, ruthless, feared and desired White Queen who has fought alongside and against the X-Men! Collects EMMA FROST #1-6.
name: Emma Frost: Higher Learning

description: Celebrating Chris Claremont and Alan Davis' return to UNCANNY X-MEN, Marvel collects their earliest collaborations on Marvel's merry mutants! In these classic stories -- some reprinted here for the first time -- the New Mutants take on Mojo and Spiral, then must contend with the alien antics of the Impossible Man; the X-Men face an enemy who can grant them their most secret desires; and Wolverine battles Sabretooth amid the infamous "Mutant Massacre"! Collects NEW MUTANTS ANNUAL #2-3, UNCANNY X-MEN ANNUAL #11, and UNCANNY X-MEN #213 and #215.
name: X-Men: Old Soldiers

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description: Wilson Fisk, the incarcerated ex-Kingpin of Crime, has a deal to propose to Iron Man: He'll use his underworld connections to help track down Captain America and his anti-Registration underground in exchange for consideration on his sentence. But can the Kingpin be trusted, or is he playing a deeper game? And how are the criminals of the Marvel Universe being forced to change the way they do business as a result of Civil War? Plus: Delve deeper in the Marvel Universe underworld in writer Frank Tieri's gritty prequel to Civil War: War Crimes! Career criminal Jackie Dio is fresh out of the Cage and looking for trouble. When he tracks down some of his old crime contacts, he discovers a lot has changed in the New York underworld - and finds more trouble than he bargained for. If he's going to have a shot at surviving, he may have to get acquainted with the shadowy figure known only as "The Consultant" - that is, if he even exists. Collects Civil War: War Crimes and Underworld #1-5.
name: TPB

description: Having squared off against Black Hornet in Japan, the new Kato travels to the states to continue the battle against the man who killed her mother. As Kato begins her quest in America, she finds herself facing off against a league of Black Hornet's Swarm ninjas, as well as a gang of super deadly, teen assassins. Kato continues her journey that will lead her directly into the smash Green Hornet series!

Fate is poised to rip Troilus and Cressida apart. When Antenor is captured by the Achaeans, they demand Cressida as part of the ransom to return Antenor to Troy. Troilus doesn't dare reveal his secret romance with Cressida. But if he doesn't, he could lose Cressida forever.
name: Betrayal 12

description: This 200-plus page blockbuster is particularly special, as it contains MORE pages of coverage on the legendary (and rare) CENTAUR COMICS line than any book previously published anywhere at any time!! Though rarely seen (even by comics historians, due to their poor distribution in the late 1930′s and early ’40′s), this storied publishing house is famous as a sort of “primordial soup” of creators and concepts; a place where styles, ideas and approaches were tried before moving on to success at bigger and better venues. With editorial product packaged by the Lloyd Jaquet studio ( the “entry point” for dozens and dozens of artists & writers who would later develop into some of the industries’ biggest stars ), CENTAUR was one of the first companies to move comic books away from newspaper strip reprints and into all-original material; heavily into action/adventure strips, and from there into lots and lots of costumed superheroes!! MEN OF MYSTERY 83 reprints no less than ELEVEN full Centaur stories, from their original source material in CENTAUR’S Amazing Man Comics, Wham Comics and Amazing Mystery Funnies. See not one but TWO full features starring AMAZING MAN, plus one each headlining The ARROW, FANTOMAN, The SHARK, AIRSUB DX, The RAINBOW, The BLACK PANTHER, REEF KINKAID (artistic great Bob Lubber’s FIRST professional art job!!) MIGHTY MAN and The BLUE FIRE, with art by Lew Glanz, Paul Gustavson, Martin Filchock, Al Plastino, and Carl Burgos !! But the special CENTAUR feature is just the beginning, as another full FIFTEEN stories culled from the archives of other publishers fill out the book, including The BLACK TERROR, CAPTAIN FREEDOM, DOLLMAN, SHOCK GIBSON, MOON GIRL, AIRBOY and MAJOR MIDNIGHT, PLUS these never previously seen (in MOM ) characters DR. FROST, The SCARAB, AMERICAN EAGLE, The FLYIN’ FOOL, The FLAMINGO and MAN O’ MARS; representing material originally published at Prize Comics, Standard/Nedor, Hillman, Continental, Fawcett, Fiction House and others. Artists on these stories include Ken Battefield, Johnny Craig, Ernie Schroeder, Leonard Frank, Bob Fujitani, Bob Powell and John Giunta. 25 full Golden Age reprint stories in all, representing some of the rarest and most esoteric material that the comic book scene of the 1940′s had to offer. Even if you consider yourself well-versed in knowledge of comics’ formative years, there is a LOT of material in this volume that we guarantee you have never seen!! As always, a great collector’s value for 218 pages of THE most sought after and hard-to-find costumed hero stories out of the 1940′s!! Reproduced in crisp and clear black & white, with full color front and back covers. Standard comic book dimensions in a bookshelf format, with a perfect-bound spine.

The stars have aligned, and the unseen clock of the universe creaks to another 'tock' as the cosmic chess game between Dreadwing and Ancient Gina jumps to a new stage of play! Ancient Gina must turn control over of the all-powerful 'Infinity Engine' to Dreadwing in order to create a key to the salvation of the universe: the alternate timeline of Alfred Steiner Peachbody! But before Dreadwing can complete the design of his insidious alteration of reality, he is ambushed by an vengeful enemy: the Kobold Queen and her legions!

name: The Adventures of The Dover Boys

description: When is letting go of your inhibitions worth the risk? International graphic novel artist Benjamin uses his trademark painterly style to depict moving portrayals of love and loss that get at the heart of what it means to throw your heart into life, no matter the consequences.
name: Vol. 1

description: Kurumi Ayaki is told by her fiance that they will have to put off the wedding--they just can't afford it yet. They both decide to work harder to earn the money, and Kurumi is given the assignment of working in the Unsolved Crimes Division, Special Unit A. This is where she meets Inspector Himuro, a young genius who is unable to leave the underground room in which he resides, and who is physically unable to feel emotions. She acts as his ears and eyes as they attempt to uncover the mystery of the serial clown murders.
name: Vol. 1

description: Having nailed the mastermind behind the serial clown murders, Kurumi decides not to quit the Special A division despite the danger...and the horrors Intendent Himuro subjects her to. Her next case leads her to a school full of delinquents...and a bomb threat which threatens the lives of everyone inside!
name: Vol. 2

description: Officer Kurumi finds the main bomb, but is prevented from disarming it by the student body president, who has discovered her and is not pleased that she's not in the classroom with everyone else. As the dark secrets of the school's past are revealed, Kurumi still has to save the lives of the students...
name: Vol. 3

description: Kurumi has been assigned to act as bodyguard for a punk kid who thinks he can take care of himself, so she pretends to be his personal assistant so he won't know that he has a bodyguard. While on duty, Kurumi's own life is put in danger when the young man's attacker closes in for the kill.
name: Vol. 4

description: Kurumi's fiance Shingo is now the suspect of a murder case, and she must turn to Inspector Himuro to help clear Shingo's name, as only he is smart enough to figure out the true identity of the person who killed the stalker. Later, Bob is suspected of being the infamous terrorist Coyote. Could these men really be guilty of such terrible crimes?
name: Vol. 5

description: Kurumi is shocked to learn that an old schoolmate of hers is not only a fuzoku girl working in a peep show, but also the victim of a brutal beheading. Himuro takes interest in the case, and assigns Kurumi to go undercover to infiltrate the peep show and discover the identity of the sole witness to the crime--the man watching Mutsumi's act when she was killed.
name: Vol. 6

description: The mystery surrounding the murder at the peepshow deepens, as Kurumi races to find the sole witness to the brutal beheading of her former schoolmate turned fuzoku girl. Unfortunately, the witness to the murder was one of the peepshow's clients, and has no interest in being found. Then, when Kurumi and Shingo head off on a mountain retreat...the festivities turn deadly when they are stranded in the woods with a psychotic madman. A madman who has already murdered five people...and may be looking to make Kurumi victim number six!
name: Vol. 7

description: Officer Kurumi Reporting: Finally, my fiancé and I are taking a well-deserved vacation to the Blood Pond Spa to clear our heads--a little time to ourselves in the mountains. But psychopaths never want to take a holiday from me. Shingo and I arrive at the spa, where we run into a group of writers who, innocuously enough, are here for an awards ceremony. When one of the scribes suddenly turns up as Best Dead Novelist, everyone else is...well, everyone else is a suspect. Later, a murder threat is sent into the Metropolitan Police Department. The instructions are simple: Go to the Ghost Building at midnight on November 10, and someone will die. I'll give you one guess who Inspector Himuro orders to be the lucky volunteer...
name: Vol. 8

description: Kurumi is investigating the mysterious death of a nurse where all the suspects have a solid alibi--they were with Kurumi at the time of death!
name: Vol. 9

description: Kurumi meets Naomi Sakaki in front of Himuro's mansion. When they go to have , and Kurumi angrily leaves the restaurant in a huff. But when a criminal mastermind kidnaps Naomi, can Kurumi come to the rescue?
name: Vol. 10

description: At the dawn of creation, the world was beautiful and peaceful. Gods and humans lived in blissful tranquility together under the Heavenly Emperor's rule. But Taishakuten rebelled against the Emperor, and a turbulent age began. 300 years later, the Guardian Warrior of the northland (Yasha, the King of his tribe), hears astrologer Kuyou's last prediction: "Six stars will strike the earth. You're the dark star that goes against heaven. Your journey begins when you find the child of a vanished race. I cannot see if the child is good or evil, but I know only this child can spin the wheel of heaven's destiny..."
name: Vol. 1

description: TOY OVERBOARD FINALE! Buzz, Jessie and Shark race to get back to the cruise ship, only to find that Andy and his mother have already left for home! Can they find their way home, or will they be lost toys forever?
name: Toy Overboard Part Four!

volume.name: Toy Story: Tales From the Toy Chest

description: Souma and Ryuu-ou join Yasha's and Ashura's journey. Led by Kujaku's advice, they go to Kusumapura, the destroyed city in the west-end of heaven, in search of the Shura Sword...which appears to be the key to find the six stars...
name: Vol. 2

description: Ashura breaks the seal of the Shura Sword and the Kusumapura collapses. Yasha, Ashura and Ryuu-ou continue their journey to find the six stars and end up being in the town of the Sky Castle--the castle of Queen Karura. Taishakuten kidnaps Karura's little sister, however things progressively get worse when tragedy befalls Karura's sister during Taishakuten's festival.
name: Vol. 3

description: Continuing on their journey, Yasha, Ashura, and Ryuu-ou arrive in the Northland at the abandoned Yasha village. The evil Vahyu, in a surprise guerilla strike, attacks the party, but hastily retreats. Taishakuten has laid a plan to lure our heroes here, as a terrible monster lives in an ice castle nearby. But Yasha is kidnapped during the night, and Ashura and Ryuu-ou depart to rescue their comrade with the help of Kujaku. Yasha's fate lies in the balance as his friends strive to save him in this exciting volume of RG Veda!
name: Vol. 4

description: The Sky Castle is shrouded in darkness as Lady Karura grieves over the death of her beloved sister. But she places herself in great danger by staying there...will she live to see Taishakuten pay for what he has done?
name: Vol. 5

description: Yasha finally meets his long-lost brother, Rasetsu. In the midst of their hometown, Rasetsu attacks Yasha to avenge their tribe. Yasha must find a way to stop fighting his brother without killing him. If things could not become worse, Koumokuten has tracked Yasha, Ashura, Lord Ryuu and Souma to the village.
name: Vol. 6

description: Shara, a human woman, invites Yasha and his crew into her home. Shara sees her husband in Yasha, and doesn't question her instinctive feelings toward him. But this moment of peace is about to be destroyed by one of their enemies!
name: Vol. 7

description: After Yasha and Shara share a moment over the death of Rasetsu, she tries to help Yasha in escaping from Koumokuten's army. But will she have to make the ultimate sacrifice in order to assure his safety? Meanwhile, Ashura's Shura Sword reveals the identity of five of the Six Stars...
name: Vol. 8

description: Five of the Six Stars have finally made it to Zenmi Castle to face the evil god king Taishakuten. As Taishakuten prepares to kill them, Kujaku shows him the "sign of evil," which is given to those who commit the most heinous of evil acts. Will the Five Stars be strong enough to defeat Taishakuten and Kujaku, or will they need the power of the Sixth Star to defeat him?
name: Vol. 9

description: In this final volume of CLAMP's epic debut, everything comes to a stunning climax. The Six Stars have gathered at the god king Taishakuten's palace for their final showdown. Ashura's seal is now lifted, and he becomes the God of Destruction, caring for nothing–but killing. Meanwhile, Kujaku reveals the meaning of the prophecy, and Taishakuten’s secret also becomes clear. And in a final clash, Ashura faces of against Yasha, and one of them will fall...
name: Vol. 10

description:
Welcome to America's newest and most popular sport: Rhysmyth! Featuring one-on-one dance battles atop a hi-tech glass court grid, when the music hits, you and your opponent dance across a digital minefield for the glory of being the most stylish Rhysmyther!

High school student Elena is looking for a little something extra to beef up her college applications. When she is thrust into the fast-paced world of Rhysmyth, she begins to get her groove on. But is Elena truly ready for the rivalry...and romance!
name: Vol. 1

description: Now Elena's on the team--to her surprise--and competing alongside the very best: the beautiful and confident Taylor, the brainy but free-spirited Diocel and the most hardcore of them all, unpredictable team captain Wahzee. But as her team prepares for their toughest match yet against archrival Mountain Ridge Prep, will Elena's skills be up to snuff? And will she be able to keep Diocel focused on the match--instead of on her?
name: Vol. 2
